  "texts": [
    "In such cases, further investigation through companion studies or direct communication with the study authors may be necessary [36].Articles that fulfilled all five quality criteria were classified as high-quality, earning a full rating of five stars or 100% quality.",
    "Additionally, articles meeting four criteria were considered to have 80% quality, those with three stars had 60% quality, two stars indicated 40% quality, and one star denoted 20% quality.",
    "If a study did not satisfy any of the quality criteria, it received no stars [37].",
    "Data synthesis and analysisThe meta-analysis was conducted when several studies reported the effects of using VR on the improvement of cognitive disorders.",
    "The standardized mean differences represented by Hedges's g to compare the treatment and control groups were calculated from the collected data."
  ]
}